23:09.111 --> 23:10.081
What?

23:13.274 --> 23:15.481
Hold everyone together.

23:17.426 --> 23:18.838
Who asked you to?

23:35.226 --> 23:37.255
Merry Christmas, happy birthday,
good Yontif.

23:37.256 --> 23:38.810
Got something for you.

23:38.811 --> 23:41.145
They found it in the trash can
on the second floor.

23:41.146 --> 23:42.165
Did they get anything from it?

23:42.166 --> 23:43.275
Not yet.

23:43.276 --> 23:46.145
Portable X-ray to Pediatrics.

23:46.146 --> 23:48.176
Portable X-ray to Pediatrics.

24:13.176 --> 24:16.136
_

24:19.918 --> 24:21.073
Sorry, sorry.

24:21.074 --> 24:22.661
Hey!

24:23.473 --> 24:25.246
Bunch of people wanted to
talk built-ins.

24:25.246 --> 24:26.522
Oh, a success?

24:26.523 --> 24:28.135
I'd say.

24:28.248 --> 24:29.591
What do you mean "he's gone?"

24:29.592 --> 24:31.582
I bought ice cream and I started talking

24:31.583 --> 24:34.201
to these girls from school,
and when I turned back...

24:34.201 --> 24:36.522
Okay. Well, he's... he's got
to be around here somewhere,

24:36.523 --> 24:37.894
- so, we'll just...
- Well, how long ago?

24:37.895 --> 24:40.523
- What?
- How long ago since you lost him?

24:41.667 --> 24:42.717
I don't know.

24:42.742 --> 24:46.328
I've... I've been looking
for him... maybe an hour?

24:51.090 --> 24:52.188
Should we get gauc?

24:52.391 --> 24:53.266
Do they make it at the table?

24:53.490 --> 24:54.600
Excuse me, have you seen a little boy?

24:54.625 --> 24:56.485
I'm gonna call 911, okay?

24:56.510 --> 24:58.640
- All right.
- Help me!

24:58.692 --> 25:00.542
- Excuse me. Have you seen a little boy?
- Have you seen a little boy, 8 years old?

25:00.567 --> 25:02.727
H-He's wearing a white T-shirt
that has my face on it.

25:02.752 --> 25:04.742
Adam! Have you seen a little boy?

25:04.767 --> 25:06.255
And he's got green eyes.

25:06.280 --> 25:07.330
Adam!

25:07.355 --> 25:08.465
Adam!

25:08.604 --> 25:10.444
- About this tall.
- Adam?!

25:10.469 --> 25:11.529
Have you seen Adam? Oh, God, Adam.

25:11.777 --> 25:12.370
Adam?

25:12.395 --> 25:15.305
Oh, God, Adam? Have you seen...

25:15.976 --> 25:16.996
He's got a white T-shirt

25:17.021 --> 25:18.825
with my picture on the front of it.

25:18.850 --> 25:20.840
- He's about 8 years old.
- Adam! Adam!

25:20.865 --> 25:21.925
Adam!

25:22.160 --> 25:24.280
- Oh, my God. Adam?
- Adam?

25:24.305 --> 25:26.115
Have you seen a little boy?

25:29.389 --> 25:31.880
- Adam?!
- Oh, my God. Adam?

25:32.438 --> 25:35.336
Why were you at Rockview Park
the night of September 2nd?

25:36.086 --> 25:37.523
I own a mini donut truck.

25:37.625 --> 25:39.076
I make my own jewelry.

25:39.076 --> 25:40.165
I run an animal rescue.

25:40.166 --> 25:41.782
I'm from the Parks Department.

25:41.884 --> 25:43.256
The PTA bought a booth.

25:43.256 --> 25:45.155
I was just with my friends.

25:45.156 --> 25:46.246
Did you see this boy?

25:46.979 --> 25:48.196
Not at my booth.

25:48.196 --> 25:49.798
That poor family.

25:50.571 --> 25:52.173
I saw that kid.

25:53.934 --> 25:56.236
I do, uh, custom cabinetry.

25:56.236 --> 25:58.215
And I had some birdhouses
out on display,

25:58.216 --> 25:59.807
and he stopped by for a minute
to look at them.

26:00.146 --> 26:01.165
Was he alone?

26:01.166 --> 26:03.521
No one seemed to be watching him.

26:03.723 --> 26:04.917
Were you alone?

26:05.552 --> 26:08.712
At the booth, and then I met
my girlfriend for dinner.

26:09.276 --> 26:10.607
And you were with your girlfriend

26:10.632 --> 26:11.318
the rest of the night?

26:11.343 --> 26:12.452
Yes, ma'am.

26:18.328 --> 26:19.865
You mind writing down her number?

26:20.552 --> 26:22.377
No. No, not at all.

26:28.433 --> 26:29.573
Anything else I can help you with?

26:32.317 --> 26:34.347
Thanks for coming down.

26:47.074 --> 26:48.802
People are boring, aren't they?

26:49.115 --> 26:51.085
Sheep with smartphones.

26:52.288 --> 26:54.903
There's no one I know in this mall.

26:55.178 --> 26:57.108
We got his jacket, John.

26:58.244 --> 26:59.724
Well, that's great. That's...

27:05.919 --> 27:07.098
I'm sorry.

27:08.130 --> 27:09.254
For what?

27:10.356 --> 27:11.855
Making things hard for you.

27:13.546 --> 27:15.395
Cases are hard.

27:15.396 --> 27:16.092
Nina...

27:16.093 --> 27:17.855
That's why it's called "work," right?

27:18.506 --> 27:19.556
Come on.

27:22.061 --> 27:23.221
Don't waste your time.

27:25.112 --> 27:26.162
Choose her.

27:27.536 --> 27:28.961
Choose your life.

27:32.827 --> 27:34.797
Single male. Blue jacket.

27:40.254 --> 27:43.184
He's been peed on, barfed on,

27:43.209 --> 27:44.951
flushed down the toilet twice...

27:45.411 --> 27:46.691
He's a survivor.

27:47.871 --> 27:48.994
Looks like it.

27:49.261 --> 27:51.291
You always needed him
when you were sick.

27:51.642 --> 27:52.854
Mom, I was 8.

27:54.111 --> 27:56.041
Oh, would you just mind, um,

27:56.066 --> 27:57.432
I think those are for someone else.

27:57.457 --> 27:59.055
It's the wrong name on the card.

28:02.159 --> 28:04.666
Okay. You're gonna be just fine.

28:04.666 --> 28:06.149
I know.

28:06.968 --> 28:08.198
I love you.

28:08.199 --> 28:10.119
I know.

28:13.069 --> 28:14.088
Hey, Mom.

28:14.089 --> 28:14.816
Yeah?

28:14.816 --> 28:16.403
I'm coming back.

28:25.918 --> 28:28.108
Bless me, Father, for I have sinned.

28:28.835 --> 28:30.988
I told a lie to fix a lie.

28:31.641 --> 28:33.516
Then you need to find the truth.

28:38.018 --> 28:39.516
I-I don't know where to look.

28:44.028 --> 28:45.374
Yes. See?

28:45.399 --> 28:47.068
That is how you cleanse your soul.

28:47.068 --> 28:48.068
I might puke.

28:48.069 --> 28:49.917
You're not gonna puke.

28:49.918 --> 28:51.097
I think it's physically
impossible to puke

28:51.098 --> 28:52.098
after one shot.

28:52.099 --> 28:54.180
Can we get two more?

28:54.888 --> 28:56.570
So, that's how you do it...

28:56.797 --> 28:58.148
you just take all your feelings,

28:58.173 --> 29:00.755
all your stupid, ugly, annoying...

29:01.068 --> 29:03.027
No. No. Those aren't my feelings.

29:03.028 --> 29:04.077
R-Right.

29:04.078 --> 29:06.007
You take y-your nice emotions,

29:06.008 --> 29:08.087
and then you just shove them down.

29:08.088 --> 29:10.937
You just stuff 'em, stuff 'em,
stuff 'em, like...

29:10.938 --> 29:12.701
like, uh, like, you know
how you pack a suitcase,

29:12.702 --> 29:14.685
how you roll everything up really tight,

29:14.710 --> 29:16.615
and then you put it exactly
where it's supposed to be,

29:16.640 --> 29:18.730
and then you sit on top of it
and then you do the zipper?

29:18.731 --> 29:20.808
- Yes.
- Yes. Exactly like that.

29:22.018 --> 29:22.856
And then what?

29:22.857 --> 29:24.882
And then you pour alcohol all over it.

29:25.898 --> 29:27.142
That can't possibly work.

29:27.143 --> 29:27.993
No, it does!

29:28.018 --> 29:31.044
It's basically been prov...
It... It's science.

29:31.081 --> 29:33.618
All right,
which has been around longer...

29:34.217 --> 29:36.740
booze or Jesus?

29:45.623 --> 29:46.672
Ah.

29:46.697 --> 29:47.716
Everything went great,

29:47.741 --> 29:49.630
he should be out of recovery very soon.

29:49.655 --> 29:51.754
Oh. Oh, good. Thank you.
Thank you so much.

29:51.779 --> 29:56.438
So, the, uh, the blockage was
here, right below his appendix.

29:56.463 --> 29:59.412
We resected two inches
of small intestine, and I...

29:59.437 --> 30:01.436
What, uh, w-what did you say?

30:01.461 --> 30:02.961
Uh, here's the transection.

30:03.221 --> 30:06.411
Uh, no. Uh, about the appendix?

30:06.448 --> 30:08.407
Uh, w-well, that's right here,

30:08.432 --> 30:10.581
but the bowel obstruction
was underneath, so...

30:10.606 --> 30:15.435
No, I-I'm sorry... could these
be someone else's scans?

30:15.512 --> 30:17.140
This is your son, Mrs. Warren.

30:17.296 --> 30:18.499
I just operated on him.

30:18.500 --> 30:22.280
No, but my son had his appendix
out when he was five.

30:23.296 --> 30:25.321
I'm pretty sure I didn't put it back in.

30:26.048 --> 30:28.636
Uh, you have three kids, right?

30:29.136 --> 30:29.922
Yes.

30:29.923 --> 30:30.915
Maybe you mixed them up.

30:31.311 --> 30:34.251
Most days I call my son the dog's name.

30:35.750 --> 30:37.473
That must be it.

30:37.586 --> 30:41.152
Uh, we'll want to observe him
for a few days, manage his pain.

31:56.760 --> 31:58.085
Adam?

32:03.629 --> 32:04.686
Adam?

32:14.348 --> 32:15.358
Ben?

32:23.642 --> 32:25.642
Hi, Mom.

32:40.037 --> 32:42.402
_

32:42.403 --> 32:44.323
Where is it?

32:56.443 --> 32:57.403
W-What are you doing?

32:57.404 --> 32:58.432
I can't find Monkey.

32:58.433 --> 33:00.761
What... what?

33:00.762 --> 33:02.183
The police must have...

33:02.184 --> 33:05.097
I don't know, when they came,
searched his room last night.

33:05.122 --> 33:06.303
What are... what are you saying?

33:06.303 --> 33:07.273
I can't his monkey!

33:07.274 --> 33:08.312
I can't find his monkey and I...

33:08.313 --> 33:09.432
And when he comes home
he's gonna need it,

33:09.433 --> 33:10.442
and I don't know where it is.

33:10.443 --> 33:11.838
Okay. Okay. It's okay.

33:11.839 --> 33:14.362
It'll be here somewhere, okay?

33:14.363 --> 33:15.681
- Yeah.
- Okay?

33:15.682 --> 33:18.382
Well, we'll find it. Okay?

33:18.383 --> 33:19.422
All right.

33:19.423 --> 33:20.642
Where is it?

33:21.413 --> 33:22.747
Where is it?

33:23.423 --> 33:25.231
Uh, where is it?

33:25.338 --> 33:28.213
_

34:22.987 --> 34:24.947
Any side effects you've noticed?

34:24.947 --> 34:26.107
I get hot. I sweat more.

34:26.108 --> 34:27.078
Hot flashes.

34:27.079 --> 34:28.927
That's the hormones.

34:28.928 --> 34:29.987
Any other effects?

34:29.987 --> 34:31.917
Uh, the rest I welcome.

34:31.918 --> 34:32.976
So no more urges?

34:34.058 --> 34:35.067
Not since I started.

34:35.068 --> 34:36.386
And that was?

34:37.047 --> 34:38.107
10 years ago.

34:38.108 --> 34:39.917
I was incarcerated.

34:39.918 --> 34:41.007
There was a study.

34:41.007 --> 34:42.985
You could volunteer.

34:49.127 --> 34:51.529
You understand you're not
required by law to do this?

34:54.607 --> 34:56.686
I'd rather be an eunuch than a monster.

34:57.148 --> 34:58.534
Every three months, then.

34:59.263 --> 35:01.042
I know the drill.

35:05.605 --> 35:06.824
I have another couple hours.

35:06.825 --> 35:09.704
I-I'll be there as soon as I can.

35:09.705 --> 35:12.506
Well, if you're tenderizing it,
it won't dry out.

35:12.735 --> 35:15.655
Just keep it warm. I'm gonna love it.

35:19.393 --> 35:20.552
Miss you, too.

35:22.775 --> 35:24.734
I ought to put a bell on you, kid.

35:24.735 --> 35:26.684
Our friend has a dog.

35:26.685 --> 35:27.744
What?

35:27.745 --> 35:29.234
They're still analyzing the fibers

35:29.235 --> 35:30.353
but it's definitely dog hair.

35:31.359 --> 35:32.851
Well, that's not nothing.

35:33.695 --> 35:35.036
Hey, stop that.

35:36.832 --> 35:37.824
What is it?

35:39.224 --> 35:40.895
That woman... rewind.

35:47.107 --> 35:48.146
That's Jane.

35:48.147 --> 35:49.551
Who's Jane?

35:50.171 --> 35:52.130
The one from the oil refinery that knew

35:52.131 --> 35:53.229
all about the bunkers.

36:22.242 --> 36:25.331
You tell anyone
about the paternity test?

36:25.332 --> 36:26.740
No.

36:29.372 --> 36:30.422
Are you going to?

36:33.292 --> 36:34.371
You want me to make you feel better

36:34.372 --> 36:36.312
or do you want me to be honest?

36:40.352 --> 36:42.040
Make me feel better.

36:44.645 --> 36:46.764
I haven't decided yet.

36:47.422 --> 36:48.540
Well...

36:54.255 --> 36:56.335
I haven't decided yet, either.

36:58.118 --> 36:59.308
Decided what?

37:03.955 --> 37:05.094
Exactly.

37:05.095 --> 37:07.104
You're drunk.

37:07.105 --> 37:11.095
Just... seems like that
because I've been drinking.

37:13.115 --> 37:15.155
Wait, wait, wait, wait.

37:18.797 --> 37:20.490
Why are you here?

37:43.152 --> 37:45.321
I don't know how to do this.

37:45.322 --> 37:48.341
Just... follow along.

38:02.797 --> 38:04.726
Dinner is served.

38:04.727 --> 38:06.719
And by "dinner" I mean, Jell-O.

38:07.190 --> 38:08.805
These are yours now, honey.

38:08.806 --> 38:10.136
There's no "Ben" here on the ward.

38:12.050 --> 38:13.260
Thank you.

38:38.691 --> 38:41.591
Loneliness is a dangerous thing.

39:06.472 --> 39:09.930
It can turn you into someone
you don't even recognize.

39:10.123 --> 39:11.539
Who is he?

39:16.423 --> 39:17.423
I... I don't know what you...

39:24.005 --> 39:25.867
Is his name Ben?

39:40.414 --> 39:42.483
I'm so sorry, mom.

39:42.508 --> 39:44.207
I'm s-sorry.

39:44.562 --> 39:45.817
Oh, God.

39:56.739 --> 39:58.649
What did you do?

40:01.945 --> 40:03.918
Man into monster.

40:04.067 --> 40:06.067
_

40:47.966 --> 40:49.926
Who's that?

40:55.613 --> 40:57.143
A friend.

41:01.898 --> 41:04.208
Lucky for me...

41:17.820 --> 41:19.060
...I was never alone.

